 Global Trade Lead, Deloitte Nigeria, Chijioke Odo (left); Director General, Nigerian Association of Chambers of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture, NACCIMA, Amb Ayoola Olukanni; 1st Deputy President, Ide John Udeagbala, Chief Executive Officer, L&Z Integrated Farms, Alhaji Muhammadu Abubakar; National President NACCIMA Hajiya Saratu Iya Aliyu and, Ambassador of the Republic of Cuba in Nigeria, Amb Carlos Sosa at the third edition of the NACCIMA-DELOITTE African Continental Free Trade Agreement (AfCFTA) Dialogue Series in Lagos…yesterday.   											PHOTO: FEMI ADEBESIN-KUTI<br />  He said for Nigeria to achieve any meaningful impact from the agreement, the private sector must unite and form a strong advocacy team to chart a positive course for the business community.
  
